readme.md
    20Ôćĺ## Benefits over plain `fetch`
    22Ôćĺ- Simpler API
    23Ôćĺ- Method shortcuts (`ky.post()`)
    24Ôćĺ- Treats non-2xx status codes as errors (after redirects)
    25Ôćĺ- Retries failed requests
    26Ôćĺ- JSON option
    27Ôćĺ- Timeout support
    28Ôćĺ- URL prefix option
    29Ôćĺ- Instances with custom defaults
    30Ôćĺ- Hooks
    31Ôćĺ- TypeScript niceties (e.g. `.json()` supports generics and defaults to `unknown`, not `any`)
    32Ôćĺ
    33Ôćĺ## Install
    35Ôćĺ```sh
    36Ôćĺnpm install ky
    37Ôćĺ```
    38Ôćĺ
    39Ôćĺ###### CDN
    41Ôćĺ- [jsdelivr](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/ky/+esm)
    42Ôćĺ- [unpkg](https://unpkg.com/ky)
    43Ôćĺ- [esm.sh](https://esm.sh/ky)
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    45Ôćĺ## Usage
    47Ôćĺ```js
    48Ôćĺimport ky from 'ky';
    49Ôćĺ
    50Ôćĺconst json = await ky.post('https://example.com', {json: {foo: true}}).json();
    51Ôćĺ
    52Ôćĺconsole.log(json);
    53Ôćĺ//=> {data: '­čŽä'}
    54Ôćĺ```
    55Ôćĺ
    56ÔćĺWith plain `fetch`, it would be:
    57Ôćĺ
    58Ôćĺ```js
    59Ôćĺclass HTTPError extends Error {}
    60Ôćĺ
    61Ôćĺconst response = await fetch('https://example.com', {
    62Ôćĺ	method: 'POST',
    63Ôćĺ	body: JSON.stringify({foo: true}),
    64Ôćĺ	headers: {
    65Ôćĺ		'content-type': 'application/json'
    66Ôćĺ	}
    67Ôćĺ});
    68Ôćĺ
    69Ôćĺif (!response.ok) {
    70Ôćĺ	throw new HTTPError(`Fetch error: ${response.statusText}`);
    71Ôćĺ}
    72Ôćĺ
    73Ôćĺconst json = await response.json();
    74Ôćĺ
    75Ôćĺconsole.log(json);
    76Ôćĺ//=> {data: '­čŽä'}
    77Ôćĺ```
    78Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    85Ôćĺ## API
    87Ôćĺ### ky(input, options?)
    89ÔćĺThe `input` and `options` are the same as [`fetch`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope/fetch), with additional `options` available (see below).
    90Ôćĺ
