  1050Ôćĺ## Tips
  1052Ôćĺ### Sending form data
  1054ÔćĺSending form data in Ky is identical to `fetch`. Just pass a [`FormData`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData) instance to the `body` option. The `Content-Type` header will be automatically set to `multipart/form-data`, overriding any existing `Content-Type` header.
  1055Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
  1109Ôćĺ### Setting a custom `Content-Type` ÔÇŽ
  1129Ôćĺ### Cancellation ÔÇŽ
  1156Ôćĺ### Proxy support (Node.js) ÔÇŽ
  1158Ôćĺ#### Native proxy support
  1160ÔćĺNode.js 24.5+ supports automatic proxy configuration via environment variables. Set `NODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1` or use the `--use-env-proxy` CLI flag.
  1161Ôćĺ
  1162Ôćĺ```sh
  1163ÔćĺNODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1 HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.example.com:8080 node app.js
  1164Ôćĺ```
  1165Ôćĺ
  1166ÔćĺOr:
  1167Ôćĺ
  1168Ôćĺ```sh
  1169Ôćĺnode --use-env-proxy app.js
  1170Ôćĺ```
  1171Ôćĺ
  1172ÔćĺSupported environment variables:
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
